==English==

===adjective===
'''mythopoetic'''

# A creative interpretation
# Given the quality of a myth or a poem, used typically in opposition to a purely factual account


==Quotes==
*"Nietzsche advocated a mythopoetic account of history rather than a purely factual account."
-Teaching Company Lecture "The Search for a meaningful Past"

*'''2000''' C A Bowers, ''Let Them Eat Data''
*: "To paraphrase Kelly (1994), we should not be suprised that Nature, having subjugated the bulk of inert matter on Earth, would go on to subjugate the '''mythopoetic''' narratives that are the basis of the moral codes that constitute this still culturally diverse world." [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=vgmlKGdMyWMC&pg=PA96&lpg=PA96&dq=mythopoetic&prev=http://books.google.com/books%3Fq%3Dmythopoetic&sig=vYr0hcrZ5MVosRfXZqLmwtNvPU4]